Notes

Distance vs Displacement

Definition (Distance).

The length of the total path travelled. Scalar quantity

Definition (Displacement).

Displacement is a vector quantity. The result should be a vector.
The MAGNITUDE of displacement, is a scalar. See diagram above
Want Distance
Not displacement
Displacement
Not Distance

We would use displacement over distance, if we actually have a change in position during the time we're measuring.

Section 2.8 Graphing Analysis of Linear Motion

Slope and Velocity
The connection between velocity slope, and the position

The idea, is that since the velocity is just the slope of the position line, the instantaneous velocity of a given position on a graph is just the slope of a line that's just glancing the function. That line will approximate the velocity really close to that point.

Slope and Acceleration
At corners, slopes are undefined
